SIMPLE: deliberation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deliberation
<hw>De*lib`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deliberatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧lib⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of deliberating, or of weighing and examining the reasons for and
against a choice or measure; careful consideration; mature
reflection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Choosing the fairest way with a calm <qex>deliberation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Montagu.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Careful discussion and examination of the reasons
for and against a measure; <as>as, the <ex>deliberations</ex> of a
legislative body or council</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deliberative</ent>⟦br⟧
